JOHANNESBURG - Woolworths is combining its Country Road and David Jones subsidiaries into a single unit. The retail giant says this will unlock the benefits and synergies of the Australian acquisitions.READ: Were the Woolies egg cartons really so bad?The move comes after David Jones s headquarters was moved from Sydney to Country Road s Melbourne base.Woolworths says the consolidation will not result in job cuts.The combined head office workforce will increase from 1,300 to 1,500.eNCA